- TASK: create an Armor class.

* As an example take the existing Weapon.cs.
* It should have the following fields: int health, int speed, int armor, ArmorType (enum), Quality (enum).
* It should have the methods generateArmor and generateSpeed and generateHealth.
* It doesn't matter what the values are, they will be edited in later stages.

- TASK: create an ArmorType enumerator.

* It should contain a few types of armor material like leather, plate, mail and so on.
* Connect it to the Armor class.




